4. **Cache-friendly iteration:** Access partsupp rows sequentially from the index (contiguous positions array), avoiding random memory access patterns

**Expected Benefits:**
- **Reduce failed lookups:** From 8M attempts to ~4K hash table checks (via index iteration)
- **Better cache locality:** Iterate contiguously through positions array instead of random access
- **Parallel efficiency:** Better load distribution when parallelizing at supplier level (4K suppliers) instead of partsupp level (8M rows)

